---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import { CONTACT_EMAIL } from '../config';

const lastUpdated = '27 June 2026';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Terms & Conditions"
  description="Terms governing use of the FramerSchool website and programs."
>
  <p class="pf-legal-meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

  <p>
    By accessing or using the FramerSchool website and related programs (the "Service"), you agree to
    these Terms & Conditions. If you do not agree, please do not use the Service.
  </p>

  <h2>Use of the Service</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>You must provide accurate information when contacting us or enrolling in programs</li>
    <li>You may not misuse the site, attempt unauthorized access, or interfere with its operation</li>
    <li>Content on the site is for general information and education; outcomes are not guaranteed</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
  <p>
    FramerSchool materials, branding, and site content are owned by us or our licensors. You may not
    copy, redistribute, or resell program materials except as expressly permitted.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-party tools</h2>
  <p>
    We may reference or link to third-party products such as Framer, Notion, or KnotCMS. Your use of
    those products is subject to their own terms and policies.
  </p>

  <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
  <p>
    The Service is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. We are not liable for indirect,
    incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of the Service to the fullest extent
    permitted by law.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We may update these terms from time to time. Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance of
    the revised terms.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about these terms: <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
